constructor.details: Sets the owner to msg.sender via Ownable constructor and stores the oracle address

params._oracle: Address of the Orakl Network oracle contract to use for price data

decimals().details: Queries the Orakl oracle for its decimal precision. This is important for correctly interpreting price values (e.g., 8 decimals means price of 100000000 = 1.00)

returns._0: The number of decimals used by the oracle for price representation

latestRoundData().details: Fetches current price data from the Orakl oracle and formats it to match Chainlink's latestRoundData interface. The startedAt and answeredInRound values use locally stored state.

returns._0: idRound The round ID from the Orakl oracle
returns._1: priceAnswer The current price as an unsigned integer (converted from int256)
returns._2: startedAt Timestamp when the round started (from local state)
returns._3: updated Timestamp when the price was last updated (from Orakl oracle)
returns._4: answeredInRound The round ID in which the answer was computed (from local state)

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setOracle(address).details: Only callable by the contract owner. This allows switching to a different oracle if needed

params._oracle: The new Orakl Network oracle contract address to use

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

answeredInRound().notice: Round ID in which the current answer was computed

constructor.notice: Initializes the Oracle contract with an Orakl Network oracle address

decimals().notice: Returns the number of decimal places for the price data

latestRoundData().notice: Returns the latest round data from the Orakl oracle in Chainlink-compatible format

oracle().notice: Address of the Orakl Network oracle contract that provides price data

price().notice: Current price of the asset tracked by this oracle

roundId().notice: Current round ID for the price feed

setOracle(address).notice: Updates the Orakl Network oracle address used for price data

startedAt().notice: Timestamp when the current round started

updatedAt().notice: Timestamp when the price was last updated
